      "gazette_notice_full_text": "GAZETTE NOTICE NO. 9105\nTHE CONSTITUTION OF KENYA\n\nTHE NATIONAL ASSEMBLY AND PRESIDENTIAL ELECTIONS ACT\n\n(Cap. 7 )\n\nTHE PRESIDENTIAL AND PARLIAMENTARY ELECTIONS REGULATIONS\n\nTHE CONSTITUTION OF KENYA REVIEW ACT\n\n(No. 9 of 2008 )\n\nTHE CONSTITUTION OF KENYA (REVIEW) REFERENDUM REGULATIONS, 2010\n\nTRANSFER OF POLLING STATION\n\nElectors) Regulations, section 38 of the Constitution of Kenya Review Act and regulation 21 (2) ( a )  of  the  Constitution  of Kenya  (Review) Referendum Regulations, the Interim Independent Electoral Commission notifies the voters of Mukuru Kaiyaba Primary School in Makadara Constituency; Code 001, Nairobi that the polling centre has been transferred to Bright Star Academy .\n\nAND THAT the reason(s) for the transfer is (are) as follows:\n\nMukuru  Kaiyaba  Primary  School  is  under  construction  and  the contractor  has  denied  access  for  polling  day  activities  for  fear  of destruction of the property in the likelihood of poll violence.\n\nDated the 2nd August, 2010.\n\nA. I. HASSAN,\n\nChairman,\n\nInterim Independent Electoral Commission.\n\nIN EXERCISE of powers conferred by Regulation 6 (1) ( d ) of the National Assembly and Presidential Elections (Registration of",
